167/* This expression evaluates to true if the relocation is for a local
168 object for which we still want to do the relocation at runtime.
169 False if we are willing to perform this relocation while building
170 the .o file. GOTOFF and GOT32 do not need to be checked here because
171 they are not pcrel. .*/
172
173#define TC_FORCE_RELOCATION_LOCAL(FIX) \
174 (GENERIC_FORCE_RELOCATION_LOCAL (FIX) \
175 || (FIX)->fx_r_type == BFD_RELOC_386_PLT32 \
176 || (FIX)->fx_r_type == BFD_RELOC_386_GOTPC \
177 || (FIX)->fx_r_type == BFD_RELOC_X86_64_GOTPCRELX \
178 || (FIX)->fx_r_type == BFD_RELOC_X86_64_REX_GOTPCRELX)

194extern int optimize_align_code;
195
196#define md_do_align(n, fill, len, max, around) \
197if ((n) \
198 && !need_pass_2 \
199 && optimize_align_code \
200 && (!(fill) \
201 || ((char)*(fill) == (char)0x90 && (len) == 1)) \
202 && subseg_text_p (now_seg)) \
203 { \
204 frag_align_code ((n), (max)); \
205 goto around; \
206 }

255/* We need to emit the right NOP pattern in .align frags. This is
256 done after the text-to-bits assembly pass, so we need to mark it with
257 the isa/tune settings at the time the .align was assembled. */
258#define TC_FRAG_TYPE struct i386_tc_frag_data
259
260#define TC_FRAG_INIT(FRAGP) \
261 do \
262 { \
263 (FRAGP)->tc_frag_data.isa = cpu_arch_isa; \
264 (FRAGP)->tc_frag_data.isa_flags = cpu_arch_isa_flags; \
265 (FRAGP)->tc_frag_data.tune = cpu_arch_tune; \
266 } \
267 while (0)
268
269#define WORKING_DOT_WORD 1
270
271/* How to generate NOPs for .nop direct directive. */
272extern void i386_generate_nops (fragS *, char *, offsetT, int);
273#define md_generate_nops(frag, where, amount, control) \
274 i386_generate_nops ((frag), (where), (amount), (control))
275
276#define HANDLE_ALIGN(fragP) \
277if (fragP->fr_type == rs_align_code) \
278 { \
279 offsetT __count = (fragP->fr_next->fr_address \
280 - fragP->fr_address \
281 - fragP->fr_fix); \
282 if (__count > 0 && __count <= MAX_MEM_FOR_RS_ALIGN_CODE) \
283 md_generate_nops (fragP, fragP->fr_literal + fragP->fr_fix, \
284 __count, 0); \
285 }
